HB 2879 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS hb2879 sub1 House Bill 2879 History OTHER VERSIONS  - Introduced Version | |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted WEST virginia legislature2025 regular sessionCommittee SubstituteforHouse Bill 2879[Reported on March 19, 2025 in the Committee on Education, then to the Committee on Finance] A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding thereto a new article, designated §18C-10-1, §18C-10-2, §18C-10-3, and §18C-10-4, relating to the creation of the West Virginia Math, Science and Special Education Teacher Scholarship Act; providing for a short title; providing for legislative findings and purpose; establishing the West Virginia Math, Science and Special Education Teacher Scholarship Act; requiring funding; setting forth the amount of scholarship money to be paid to educators who satisfy the thresholds; and creating a sunset provision. ARTICLE 10. west virginia MATH & Science teacher scholarship act. §18C-10-1. Short title. This article shall be known and may be cited as the "West Virginia Math, Science and Special Education Teacher Scholarship Act." §18C-10-2. Legislative findings and purpose. (a) The Legislature hereby finds and declares that:(1) Every West Virginia student should have access to education and training that will lead directly to quality employment opportunities within the state. For West Virginia to retain and attract teachers and educators in this particular field, our state must ensure that qualified teachers within West Virginia are incentivized to stay and work in West Virginia schools. (2) West Virginia currently faces a shortage of educators, particularly with those who have specialized training in the mathematics, science and special education fields, which has likely contributed to underperformance in student test scores. (b) The purpose of this article is to provide existing and upcoming West Virginia educators with incentives to remain in West Virginia and pursue a career in educating students in the fields of mathematics, science and special education through the creation of a scholarship program designed to recruit and retain teachers in mathematics and science. §18C-10-3. West Virginia Math & Science Teacher Scholarship Act; funding. (a) There is hereby created a scholarship program known as the "West Virginia Math,  Science and Special Education Teacher Scholarship", which shall be administered by the vice chancellor for administration pursuant to §18B-4-2 of this code. (b) The scholarship program shall be available to all West Virginia certified teachers with specializations in a mathematics, science or special education. (1) A math, science or special education teacher who has been employed in an elementary or secondary public school in this state for three years shall be eligible for up to $2,000 in debt relief through this scholarship. (2) A math, science or special education teacher who has been employed in an elementary or secondary public school in this state for six years shall be eligible for up to $4,000 in debt relief: Provided, That the total debt relief per teacher may not exceed $4000.(c) Funding for this program shall be appropriated through a line item in the budget. §18C-10-4. Eligibility requirements; agreements; sunset provision. (a) To be eligible for the West Virginia Math, Science and Special Education Teacher Scholarship Program, an individual shall satisfy the following requirements: (1) Be a citizen of the United States and have been a resident of West Virginia for at least one year immediately preceding the date of application for the scholarship;(2) Have completed at least a master's degree in education, with a specialization in mathematics, science or special education;(3) Be employed by an elementary or secondary public school in this state for a minimum of three years for the initial $2,000 of debt relief and six years for the additional $2,000 of debt relief;(4) Fill a position that qualifies as mathematics, science or special education position under applicable State Board of Education rules and policies; and(5) Have available debt to qualify, as scholarship funds to recipients may not exceed any debt owed at the time of award. Applicants who have a debt balance which is less than the award amount may not receive more than the amount of the debt owed.(b) The West Virginia Math, Science and Special Education Teacher Scholarship Program shall begin on January 1, 2026 and shall sunset on January 1, 2036. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


